{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe live Jira/LLM external tier (`tests/external/`) runs only on `workflow_dispatch`\n(`.github/workflows/external-integration.yml`), which sets `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1` and maps\n`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`/`OPENAI_API_KEY` but **no `JIRA_*` secrets** and does **not install the\n`acli` binary** â€” and `test_link_sync_roundtrip_live.py::_live_jira_ready()` gates on BOTH\n(`creds and shutil.which(\"acli\")`). So the live Jira round-trip can only ever SKIP: Jira\nAPI/SDK drift merges through normal CI with no real integration signal, and nothing fails a\nrun in which the whole external tier silently skips. VALIDATED.\n\nCorrection to the earlier framing: the live test is NOT read-only â€” it calls `create_issue`\ntwice + `set_relationship`, then in a `try/finally` deletes every artifact it created (links\nthen issues). It makes REAL, self-cleaning Jira mutations against whatever project the creds\npoint at, so it requires a DEDICATED disposable test project, not a shared one.\n\n## What\n1. **Workflow** (`external-integration.yml`): add an `on.schedule` trigger with the exact cron\n   `0 6 * * 1` (Mondays 06:00 UTC, weekly) alongside `workflow_dispatch`, and MIRROR the\n   established `reconcile-bridge.yml` convention\n   EXACTLY (not an ad-hoc variant):\n   - Jira env, sourced the SAME way reconcile-bridge does: `JIRA_URL: ${{ vars.JIRA_URL }}`,\n     `JIRA_USER: ${{ vars.JIRA_USER }}` (repo VARIABLES, not secrets), and\n     `JIRA_API_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.JIRA_API_TOKEN }}` (the only secret), and `JIRA_PROJECT: ${{ vars.JIRA_PROJECT }}` (the live Jira tests read it for the target project).\n   - the `acli` install, reusing reconcile-bridge's THREE companion steps verbatim in shape:\n     the `cache-acli` cache step, the `Download + verify + install acli` step (pinned\n     `vars.ACLI_VERSION` + `vars.ACLI_SHA256`, sha256-checked), AND the `Add acli to PATH and\n     authenticate` step exactly as reconcile-bridge does it: `sudo ln -sf \"$HOME/.acli/acli\"\n     /usr/local/bin/acli` (symlink the binary into the on-PATH `/usr/local/bin`, NOT\n     `$GITHUB_PATH`), then `echo \"$JIRA_API_TOKEN\" | acli jira auth login --site \"$JIRA_URL\"\n     --email \"$JIRA_USER\" --token`. Without this step `shutil.which(\"acli\")` and the live auth\n     both fail, so the Jira tests still skip.\n2. **Fail-on-all-skip Jira canary** â€” deterministic, marker-based (NOT skip-string matching,\n   which is fragile across the tier's many distinct skip reasons), and SELF-MAINTAINING (no\n   hardcoded module list, so a future Jira module is auto-covered). All Jira live modules share\n   one gate signature: a module-level `_live_jira_ready()` + `_skip = skipif(not\n   _live_jira_ready(), â€¦)` (currently `test_link_sync_live.py`, `test_link_sync_roundtrip_live.py`,\n   `test_reconcile_live.py`, `test_verified_fake_contract_live.py`, but the hook keys off the\n   signature, not this list).\n   - Register a `jira_live` marker (pyproject `[tool.pytest.ini_options].markers`).\n   - In `tests/external/conftest.py`, a `pytest_collection_modifyitems` hook AUTO-APPLIES the\n     `jira_live` marker to every collected item whose `item.module` defines `_live_jira_ready`\n     (i.e. every Jira-gated module, present or future) â€” no per-file `@pytest.mark` edits, no\n     enumeration to drift.\n   - A `pytest_sessionfinish(session, exitstatus)` hook (which sets a nonzero `session.exitstatus` to fail the run) that, when\n     `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is truthy, REPORTS the `jira_live` executed-vs-skipped counts and\n     FAILS the session (nonzero exit) iff â‰Ą1 `jira_live` test was COLLECTED but ZERO executed\n     (passed or failed) â€” exactly the \"Jira secrets/acli missing, no real signal\" condition.\n     Membership is the marker (deterministic), so unrelated always-on tests\n     (`test_model_requests_enabled`, `test_deps_live`) neither mask nor trip it.\n   - When `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is unset (the default suite, tier inert via the opt-in guard),\n     the hook is a no-op.\n3. **Tests**:\n   - a behavioral test of the fail-on-all-skip hook over SIMULATED session reports: a session\n     where all `jira_live` tests skipped (with `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1`) makes the hook signal\n     failure; a session where â‰Ą1 `jira_live` test executed passes; and an unset\n     `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is a no-op. (Drive the hook function directly with constructed\n     report objects â€” no live creds needed.)\n   - a config-as-artifact test asserting `external-integration.yml` declares an `on.schedule`\n     trigger, maps `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/`JIRA_API_TOKEN` into the external job env, AND\n     installs `acli` / puts it on PATH (a drift guard mirroring the repo's YAML-artifact tests).\n\n## Scope\n- `.github/workflows/external-integration.yml` â€” schedule + JIRA_* env + acli install/PATH/auth.\n- `pyproject.toml` â€” register the `jira_live` pytest marker.\n- `tests/external/conftest.py` â€” register-free auto-marking (`pytest_collection_modifyitems`\n  keyed on `_live_jira_ready`) + the marker-scoped fail-on-all-skip session hook + report.\n- A test module (e.g. `tests/unit/test_external_canary.py`) â€” the hook behavior + workflow wiring.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The workflow declares `on.schedule` with cron `0 6 * * 1`; sources `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/`JIRA_PROJECT`\n      from `vars.*` and `JIRA_API_TOKEN` from `secrets.*` (matching reconcile-bridge.yml); and\n      installs `acli` + symlinks it onto PATH + authenticates (the cache / download-verify-install\n      / add-to-PATH-and-authenticate steps). A config-as-artifact test pins the cron, the Jira\n      env wiring, and the acli PATH/auth step.\n- [ ] A `jira_live` marker is registered and AUTO-APPLIED (via a collection hook keyed on\n      `_live_jira_ready`) to every Jira-gated live module; the\n      conftest hook FAILS an external session (with `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1`) iff â‰Ą1 `jira_live`\n      test was collected but zero executed (all skipped), PASSES when a `jira_live` test\n      executed, and is a no-op when `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is unset â€” asserted by a behavioral\n      test driving the hook over constructed report objects.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The operator configures the `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER` repo VARIABLES,\n      the `JIRA_API_TOKEN` SECRET, and the `ACLI_VERSION`/`ACLI_SHA256` repo variables, and\n      provisions a DEDICATED disposable Jira test project (these require GitHub repo-admin + a\n      Jira project and cannot be done from the code change). CONCRETE evidence to record as a\n      comment on this ticket: the URL of a manual `workflow_dispatch` run of the\n      `external-integration` workflow whose `external` job is GREEN with the live Jira\n      round-trip test EXECUTED (passed, not skipped) â€” i.e. the fail-on-all-skip canary did NOT\n      fire â€” plus the run id/timestamp. A blank \"done\" without that run URL does not satisfy it.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783817830837665001,"uuid":"2a608f39-c227-451c-981e-28cc845aa3af"}